  <his_func>&lt;p&gt;The London Missionary Society was established by Anglican and Protestant church leaders in 1794/1795. The aim was missionary work around the world without being bound to a denomination. In 1796 the first missionaries were sent out.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Missionary work in Demerara began in 1808 after a request from H.H. Post, owner of the "Le Resouvenir" cotton plantation on the East Coast. There John Wray started his missionary work among the slaves in February 1808; John Davies followed in January 1809 to take care of a school.&lt;/p&gt;</his_func>
